PANDORA is the box that once, opened can never be closed.
(Prometheus did this)

The authors thinks that once RPL-style "mesh" routing is loose on 
citizen controlled mobile devices that citizens will no longer be
held hostage to incumbent telcos that dominate the broadband
"Internet".

This program is a set of tools that runs under the Linux kernel:
on netbooks, laptops, and on phones like the Google Android and Nokia N800.  

Using IETF (to be) standard RPL (a product of the ROLL WG), people can create
mesh networks in IPv6 space.

Michael Richardson <mcr@sandelman.ca>,
Ottawa, Ontario, October 2009 (on a train, where Internet is broken)




